# Phase A: Tactile UI + Chat/Notifications on Mocks -- Implementation Plan

## Overview

This plan covers five sub-phases (A1 through A5), each producing a working build. The total implementation touches **17 existing files** and creates **22 new files**, for a total of **39 files** across all sub-phases.

The base path for all files is `C:\Users\yakik\Documents\projects\rearden\apps\web\src`.

---

## A1: Tactile Interaction System

**Goal**: Make every click feel physical. Spring animations everywhere, subtle grain texture, inset shadow press effects.

**Files modified: 9 | Files created: 0 | Total: 9**

### 1. `C:\Users\yakik\Documents\projects\rearden\apps\web\src\styles\_variables.scss`

Add spring configuration SCSS variables at the bottom of the file (after the Transitions section). These are documentation-level constants -- the actual spring physics live in Motion v12 JS, but we define SCSS transition values for CSS-only active states:

```scss
// Spring configs (for reference, actual springs in JS)
// $springStiff: stiffness 400, damping 25, mass 1
// $springMedium: stiffness 300, damping 30, mass 1
// $springGentle: stiffness 200, damping 20, mass 1

// Tactile press
$pressScale: 0.95;
$pressTranslateY: 2px;
$shadowInsetPress: inset 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
$shadowInsetPressLight: inset 0 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
```

### 2. `C:\Users\yakik\Documents\projects\rearden\apps\web\src\components\Button\Button.tsx`

